<br>
Off the top of my head:<br>
<br>
Maiden's Eye (Spectral Wolves)<br>
 - Ravenous Beasts are TOO high for Call of Karana<br>
<br>
Chardok (Any chokidai xxx)<br>
<br>
Siren's (Seahorses, as well as walruses, sea elephants, etc.)<br>
<br>
West Wastes (velium hounds, brontotheriums, etc.)<br>
<br>
In a wacky grind group in Maiden's Eye the other night (2 necros, 2 druids, cleric, ranger) - I kept a spectral wolf charmed for about 2 hours (with repeated recharms) - a pet that doubles for 150ish is a pretty nice asset; and if he never broke charm, I'd call that especially powerful.<br>
<br>
As far as this including mobs other than animals, that seems incredibly hard to believe, I see no evidence that this would not be an animal only ability. <p><img src=http://personal.jax.bellsouth.net/jax/b/m/bmalek/Signature.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/14/01 3:10:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dire Charm Questions</span><hr size=1> Spectral Wolves in Maiden's, Cokidais, Seahorses in SG, half the Drakel Dire Wolves in Kael and all the animals in WW are charmable with Call of Karana, but that's not the 49 charm.  Which are charmable with 49 charm?  Probably only the Chokidais, if 49 is the level limit.<br>
